        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(durable): add coordination projections for agent work",
        "body": "Depends on:\n- #97507 (`docs: propose durable agent coordination kernel`)\n- #97508 (`feat(durable): add opt-in agent coordination kernel`)\n- PR-A: durable upgrade/restart safety branch `codex/openclaw-durable-batch-a-upgrade-safety`\n\nThis PR adds the first product-facing durable coordination slice without turning OpenClaw into a general-purpose workflow engine. It gives long-running agent work stable intake identity, branch/report route identity, and an optional projection into existing Task Flow state.\n\nWhat changed:\n- Adds `acceptDurableWorkflowIntake`, a small idempotent frontdoor helper for creating a durable run, optional input ref, and optional initial step.\n- Adds durable report routes for branch-aware progress/fan-in metadata.\n- Adds a Task Flow projection bridge that maps a durable run into Task Flow status/state/wait metadata.\n\nWhy this matters:\n- Multi-step agent work needs stable IDs that survive gateway restart and do not rely on one chat/session channel as the source of truth.\n- Branch/report routes make fan-out/fan-in state explicit, reducing the chance that parallel subagent results are mixed together.\n- Task Flow integration shows how Durable Core can complement an existing OpenClaw primitive instead of creating a parallel orchestration product.\n\nPartial acceptance path:\n- Commit 1 (`feat(durable): add workflow intake primitive`) is independent.\n- Commit 2 (`feat(durable): add branch report routes`) is independent once the durable store/ref primitives from #97508 exist.\n- Commit 3 (`feat(durable): project runs into taskflow state`) is intentionally isolated. If maintainers want the core intake/routes first but want to revisit Task Flow projection semantics, this final commit can be dropped or deferred without invalidating the first two commits.\n\nBoundaries:\n- No AICOS names, schemas, or MCP-specific semantics.\n- No Workboard dependency from Durable Core.\n- No worker loop or retry-policy changes in this PR.\n- Projection writes are best-effort and must not break durable recovery or live agent execution.\n\nReview notes:\n- The branch is stacked on #97508 and PR-A, so the GitHub diff may include earlier dependency commits until they land.\n- The intended review range after PR-A is three commits: intake, branch routes, Task Flow projection.\n\nValidation:\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit.config.ts src/durable/intake.test.ts src/durable/routes.test.ts src/durable/taskflow-bridge.test.ts src/tasks/task-flow-registry.test.ts`\n- Full stacked check also passed on PR-C: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit.config.ts src/durable src/tasks/task-flow-registry.test.ts`\n",
        "branch": "codex/openclaw-durable-batch-b-coordination-projection",
